rComments: Professor Dittrich is a great prof in UTM's Professional Writing and Communication Department. He offers two courses. I've taken both with him and the format is pretty much the same. If you actively participate in group discussions in his class, consider you've gotten an easy participation mark. He is also nice and approachable.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Group projects', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Great prof! Took both WRI310 and WRI340 with him and they both proved really interesting. He's lad back, easy to talk to and really helpful. Coursework wasn't that bad, around 4 assignments (which is nothing compared to other WRI courses) and a group project. Particpating in discussion will get your grade up.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Dittrich is a good professor. He can make lectures really interesting and seems very down-to-earth. He does assign weekly scholarly readings and I find he marks harder than the other writing profs. The course was a mix of interesting (music) and a mix of non-interesting (economic and political discussion).
He's smart, laid back, helpful, and easy to talk to. From what I noticed, he enjoys teaching the material and he appreciates creativity. He's also pretty cute.
Amazing, easy going prof. Very funny. Enjoyed his personality and how he brought it towards the class. Pretty tough marker though. Nonetheless, great guy

I LOVE this prof. Genuinely so so nice. He's so laid back and although his lectures get a little dry at times, his editing sessions are great. Definitely my favourite PWC prof, and one of my favourite UTM profs-- highly recommended :)
try to speak up in class. fair marker, great prof. and he's cute!
